The paper discusses the use of computational techniques to enhance fact-checking, which involves natural language processing and knowledge representation. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper frames the fact-checking problem as a network problem, which could also place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
